---
title: Maple-Rosemary Roasted Half Chicken with Fingerling Potatoes, Carrots & Lemon Pepper Sauce
description: Roasted chicken, potatoes, and veggies—one of our ultimate comfort food combinations—comes together in just an hour with this simple sheet pan dinner. You'll pair a juicy half-chicken with tender fingerling potatoes, carrots, and onions, then drizzle with a maple-Dijon-rosemary glaze. A creamy lemon pepper sauce rounds out this instant winner.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6732477b1cd01ca44ffc2ba2-de9d28f6.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6732477b1cd01ca44ffc2ba2-en-US.pdf
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/maple-rosemary-roasted-half-chicken-6732477b1cd01ca44ffc2ba2
time required: 1 hour
course: main course
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 1380 kcal
  fat: 93 g
  saturated fat: 33 g
  carbohydrates: 68 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 65 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 600 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Halve @fingerling potatoes{12%oz}. Halve, peel, and cut @onion{1} into 1-inch wedges.

Toss carrots, potatoes, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Spread out in a single layer on one side of sheet (for 4, spread veggies out across entire sheet).

Pat @half chicken{1} dry with #paper towels{} and season generously all over with @salt{generous} and @pepper{generous}. (TIP: See a feather? Simply grip the end using a paper towel and pull!) Place chicken, skin side up, on opposite side of sheet from veggies (for 4 servings, add chicken to a second sheet).

Roast on top rack until chicken is browned and cooked through and veggies are tender, ~{35-45%minutes} (for 4, roast chicken on top rack and veggies on middle rack, swapping positions halfway through).

> To ensure chicken is cooked through, insert a thermometer into the innermost part of the thigh and breast (avoiding any bones). Once chicken is cooked, the bones may still appear pink—this is OK!

While chicken and veggies roast, zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, remaining @garlic powder{1%tsp}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and as much lemon zest as you like. Taste and season with @salt{pinch} and plenty of @pepper{plenty} (and more lemon juice and zest if desired!). Refrigerate until ready to serve.

Once chicken and veggies are done, let chicken rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

Strip @rosemary{1/4%oz} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings). Reserve remaining whole leaves for garnish.

In a #small pan{} over medium-high heat, combine @maple syrup{2%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, chopped rosemary, @butter{3%tbsp}, @water{2%tbsp}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{to taste} (6 TBSP butter and 1⁄4 cup water for 4). Cook, whisking, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Glaze should be glossy; if it seems greasy, add a splash of water and continue to cook over medium-high heat, whisking, until smooth and thickened.

Transfer chicken and veggies to a #serving plate{}; drizzle with glaze and garnish with reserved rosemary leaves. Serve family style with creamy lemon pepper sauce and any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.